    "actor_description": "A memory comes up—clear enough, like a photograph held at arm’s length. I can name the place, the faces, the small details, but it doesn’t tug the way it should. No sweetness, no ache—just this muted replay, as if my mind is thumbing through old pages because there’s nothing better to do. I’m here, but only technically. The present feels thin; the future feels even thinner.",
    "description_text": "{actor} grows distant in a flat way, gaze slipping past what’s in front of them. Their expression doesn’t brighten or crumple—just dulls, like a thought has pulled them sideways. They pause mid-action, then resume with reduced urgency, responding a beat late as if their mind is replaying something old without really feeling it.",
    "alternate_descriptions": {
